{% extends "index.twig" %}

{% block main %}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Projects</h2>

      <p>Below you can find projects I've been working on regarding composition, system design and narrative design. To view my autonomous compositions, please visit the <a href="{{ base_path_for(pages.compositions) }}">compositions</a> page. Most of my side software projects can be found on my <a href="{{ links.github }}">GitHub</a> profile.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="tabs" data-tag-tabs>
      <ul>
        <li class="is-active"><a data-tag="*">All</a></li>
        <li><a data-tag="composition">Composition</a></li>
        <li><a data-tag="system_design">System design</a></li>
        <li><a data-tag="narrative_design">Narrative design</a></li>
        <li><a data-tag="paper">Papers</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="composition, system_design, narrative_design">
        <div class="card-image">
          <figure class="image is-16by9">
            <iframe class="has-ratio" src="{{ projects.invisible_wings.embed }}" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Invisible Wings</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">Composition</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">Narrative design</span>
          </div>

          <p><i>Invisible Wings</i> is an interactive visual novel which takes place in a modern fantasy world, characterized by constant tensions between humans, faeries and their hybrid chlidren. The story follows Dawn, a young hybrid, and her quest for answers to her own identity and self-acceptance.</p>
          <p>Aside from my work as composer and technical audio designer, I have set up this game from scratch on my own, as the result of my dream of creating a narrative fantasy game. Furthermore I took the lead in the conceptualizing and developing the game, collaborating with a screenwriter, an illustrator and voice actors in the process. Upon finishing the demo, <i>Invisible Wings</i> will be released on Steam and Itch.io.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.invisible_wings.link }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fas fa-link"></i></span>
              <span>Visit website</span>
            </a>
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.invisible_wings.steam }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-steam"></i></span>
              <span>Steam</span>
            </a>
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.invisible_wings.itch }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-itch-io"></i></span>
              <span>Itch.io</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="composition, system_design, narrative_design">
        <div class="card-image">
          <figure class="image is-16by9">
            <img src="{{ projects.hope_remember.image }}" alt="Hope/Remember">
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Hope/Remember</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">Composition</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">Narrative design</span>
          </div>

          <p>Together with Arto Koistinen I worked on <i>Hope/Remember</i> for the 47th Ludum Dare game jam in October 2020. This game is a narrative game reminiscent of okd school top down RPGs, which a story centered around a time loop in the week op Halloween. I created the audio and music for the game, as well as helped brainstorming and conceptualizing the idea and narrative.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.hope_remember.link }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fas fa-gamepad"></i></span>
              <span>Play game</span>
            </a>
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.hope_remember.soundcloud }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-soundcloud" data-fa-transform="shrink-7" data-fa-mask="fas fa-square"></i></span>
              <span>SoundCloud</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="composition, system_design">
        <div class="card-image">
          <figure class="image is-16by9">
            <img src="{{ projects.ocarime.image }}" alt="Ocarime">
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Ocarime</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">Composition</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
          </div>

          <p><i>Ocarime</i> is a network of composers, sound designers and software developers. Our collaborative is composed of different audio specialists, creating a unique network to deliver carefully designed audio for both commercial and personal use.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.ocarime.link }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fa fa-link"></i></span>
              <span>Visit website</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="composition, system_design">
        <div class="card-image">
          <figure class="image is-16by9">
            <div class="scale">
              <iframe class="has-ratio" src="{{ projects.ocarime_the_game.embed }}" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Ocarime: The Game</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">Composition</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
          </div>

          <p><i>Ocarime: The Game</i> is a prototype for an interactive portfolio website for the members of <i>Ocarime</i>. In the game the player can listen to the music and view the portfolio of the team members of <i>Ocarime</i> by interacting with the environment and objects. The game itself acts as a portfolio item for the team as well, and shows what its members are capable of creating.</p>
          <p>All team members, including me, composed a musical piece to be played back in the prototype, which together form a nonlinear composition based on the location of the player. Furthermore I developed most of the engine for the game in HTML5 and JavaScript.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.ocarime_the_game.link }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fas fa-gamepad"></i></span>
              <span>Play game</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="system_design, paper">
        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Nonlinear music in narrative games</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">Paper</span>
          </div>

          <p>In this article I have researched the different functions of nonlinear music in narrative games, and how the music design used in the game contributes to that function. These findings are used in the development of a design strategy and its application in narrative games in my own portfolio.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.thesis.read }}">
              <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf"></i></span>
              <span>Read paper</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

