      <div class="card has-background-primary has-text-light" data-tag-collapse data-tags="composition, system_design">
        <div class="card-image">
          <figure class="image is-16by9">
            <iframe class="has-ratio" src="{{ projects.room_of_doom.embed }}" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="has-text-light">Room Of Doom</h3>

          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-dark">Composition</span>
            <span class="tag is-dark">System design</span>
          </div>

          <p><i>Room Of Doom</i> is a two-player co-op party platformer created by Games & Interaction students of HKU in 2018. I worked on this student project as composer and sound designer. The integration of the music in the game was done using the FMOD audio middleware.</p>

          <div class="buttons">
            <a class="button is-link is-inverted" href="{{ projects.room_of_doom.soundcloud }}">
